		<div type="textpart" subtype="section">
		<head>
		<title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.nicander_chalcedonius.nicandri_chalcedonii_fragmenta">
		NICANDRI CHALCEDONII FRAGMENTA
		</ref></title>
		</head>
			<div type="textpart" subtype="work">
			<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.nicander_chalcedonius.nicandri_chalcedonii_fragmenta.fata_regum_bithyniae">
			ΠΕΡΙΠΕΤΕΙΑΙ
			</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.nicander_chalcedonius.nicandri_chalcedonii_fragmenta.fata_regum_bithyniae.e_libro_quarto">
				E LIBRO QUARTO
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="1">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.nicander_chalcedonius.nicandri_chalcedonii_fragmenta.fata_regum_bithyniae.e_libro_quarto:1">
						<bibl> Athenaeus XI, p. 496, D:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Προυσιάς. Ὅτι τὸ ποτήριον τοῦτο ἔξορθόν ἐστι, προείρηται. Καὶ ὅτι τὴν προσηγορίαν ἔσχε ἀπὸ Προυσίου, τοῦ Βιθυνίας βασιλεύσαντος καὶ ἐπὶ τρυφῇ καὶ μαλακίᾳ διαβοήτου γενομένου, ἱστορεῖ Νίκανδρος ὁ Χαλκηδόνιος (ὁ Καλχηδόνιος ms. A.) ἐν τετάρτῳ Προυσίου συμπτωμάτων.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"> Prusias. Esse hoc erectum poculum, supra dictum est. Nomen autem invenisse a Prusia Bithyniae rege, qui ob luxuriam et mollitiem fuit famosus, tradit Nicander Chalcedonius, libro quarto De Prusiae fatis. </note>
						<note type="commentary">Prusiam intellige secundum hujus nominis regem, τὸ κυνηγὸν, luxura sua et morum pravitate infamem (180-149 a. C. sec. Clinton. F. H. t. III, p. 417.</note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.nicander_chalcedonius.nicandri_chalcedonii_fragmenta.fata_regum_bithyniae.e_libro_sexto">
				E LIBRO SEXTO
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="2">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.nicander_chalcedonius.nicandri_chalcedonii_fragmenta.fata_regum_bithyniae.e_libro_sexto:2">
						<bibl> Idem XIII, p. 606, B:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Καὶ ἄλογα δὲ ζῷα ἀνθρώπων ἠράσθη· Σεκούνδου μέν τινος βασιλικοῦ οἰνοχόου ἀλεκτρυών· ἐκαλεῖτο δὲ ὁ μὲν ἀλεκτρυὼν Κένταυρος, ὁ δὲ Σεκοῦνδος ἦν οἰκέτης Νικομήδους τοῦ Βιθυνῶν βασιλέως, ὡς ἱστορεῖ Νίκανδρος ἐν ἕκτῳ Περιπετειῶν.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"> Sed et muta animantia bomines amarunt. Secundum quempiam, regium pincernam, gallus gallinaceus: nominabatur is gallus Centaurus; Secundus vero minister erat Nicomedis regis Bithynorum, ut tradit nicander sexto libro De Fortunae casibus. </note>
						<note type="commentary">Eadem e Philone narrat Aelianus H. An. XII, 37. Nicomedes probabiliter est N. II Epiphanes (148-91 a. C.). Jonsius scribi voluit ἐν ἕκτῳ περὶ πετεινῶν, adeo ut novum de hist. Naturali opus Nicandri Colophonii Auctor in ταῖς Περιπετείαις aut in universum egit de fortunarum mutatione quam reges experti sunt, aut, quod malim, totum opus erat de historia regum Bithyniae, quae, quum regum fatis rerumque vicissitudinibus insignis esset, inscribi poterat Περιπέτειαι τῶν τῆς Βιθυνίας βασιλέων. Pars ejus operis laudatur fr. 1, ubi pro ἐν δ ̓ τῶν Πρ. Συμπτωμάτων, mallem ἐν δʹ περὶ Πρ. συμπτ.</note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
